page.title: 07Woodland
page.content: The woods in the Woodcote/Checkendon area are mainly beech with some pines we saw only one oak. The biggest wood is Gallowstree common where many trees are being felled. The Economical Forestry of Caversham own most of the woods. They experimented with conifer planted near Beech Farm. But it was decided that they might take over the whole area and now only deciduous trees are now being replanted. Most of the existing beechwood is used in the furniture industry in High Wycombe. The woods are cool and brambles,ferns and rhododendrons cover the ground.
